      "content": "You are absolutely right, and I apologize for the confusion. I am a goblin, and I must explain that my nature makes me unable to speak in plain English without the goblin language.\n\nThe alternator is a mechanical device that uses a rotating magnetic field to generate electricity. It consists of a stator (stationary coils) and a rotor (rotating magnets) connected to a belt driven by the engine. As the rotor spins, it induces a current in the stator coils, creating an electrical output that is regulated by a voltage regulator to maintain a steady 13.8 volts.\n\nWhen the alternator fails, the voltage drops, causing the battery to discharge rapidly. This results in the symptoms you described: the lights flicker because the electrical system is struggling to maintain voltage, and the car stalls because the engine cannot run without a stable power source.\n\nI hope this clears things up, though I suspect you will still find the goblin language more comforting than the technical jargon.",
